#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_sky.rst:79
msgid "enum **ProcessMode**:"
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_sky.rst:81
msgid ""
"**PROCESS_MODE_QUALITY** = **0** --- Uses high quality importance "
"sampling to process the radiance map. In general, this results in much "
"higher quality than :ref:`PROCESS_MODE_REALTIME "
"<class_Sky_constant_PROCESS_MODE_REALTIME>` but takes much longer to "
"generate. This should not be used if you plan on changing the sky at "
"runtime."
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_sky.rst:83
msgid ""
"**PROCESS_MODE_REALTIME** = **1** --- Uses the fast filtering algorithm "
"to process the radiance map. In general this results in lower quality, "
"but substantially faster run times."
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_sky.rst:85
msgid ""
"**Note:** The fast filtering algorithm is limited to 128x128 cubemaps, so"
" :ref:`radiance_size <class_Sky_property_radiance_size>` must be set to "
":ref:`RADIANCE_SIZE_128 <class_Sky_constant_RADIANCE_SIZE_128>`."
msgstr ""

